						               													<description>Have you ever written a letter and mailed it?&amp;#10;Did you have friends or pen pals?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;That is why we ventured into this game that invites and challenges us to write letters. Some unexpected. Others, perhaps, waiting for the right time to see the light. Postdata reconnects us with the universe of the manuscript, where we can capture ideas, feelings, wishes, desires... where hope and expectation are the protagonists.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The deck has 50 cards: 15 possible recipients, 10 letter types, 10 epistolary fragments and 15 postscripts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players choose (or randomly select) one of each, and write a letter according to them. Who you are writing to, which type of letter, a fragment to inspire you, and a postscript option to use to finish the letter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then choose the best letter and send it!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
